external_knowledge:
- "most active department" refers to the department with the highest number of activities or records, which in this context is department ID 1;
- "latest entries" refer to the records created most recently within each user's set of records in the specified department;
- "three most recent creations per user" means selecting only the top 3 records based on the most recent creation time for each distinct user in the department.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(record_id) AS record_count
FROM records
WHERE status = 'active';

SELECT u.username, d.name AS department_name
FROM users u
JOIN departments d ON u.department_id = d.department_id;

SELECT display_name
FROM records
WHERE record_id = 1;

SELECT MIN(created_on) AS earliest_creation, COUNT(record_id) AS total_records, department_id
FROM records
GROUP BY department_id;

SELECT COUNT(record_id) AS active_record_count
FROM records
WHERE status = 'active' AND created_by = 1;

SELECT AVG(value) AS average_value
FROM attributes
WHERE record_id = 1;
